{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"678d238f-8776-433a-b1fb-b78f68d600e5","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework Support (MSTest v3 requires .NET ≥ 6.0 or .NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2):**\n\n| Target | Compatible? |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped — upgrade to `net6.0`+ |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped — upgrade to `net6.0`+ |\n\n**Package Changes:**\nMSTest v3 consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** package. You'd replace both references with:\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\n**To migrate**, you need to:\n1. Replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported TFMs (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. Replace the two MSTest package references with the single `MSTest` package.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"439930e3-2bbf-48fe-b14f-df6022a89634","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me recall:\n\nMSTest v3 requires:\n- .NET 6.0 or later (for .NET Core/5+)\n- .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later\n\nSo:\n- `net5.0` — .NET 5 is NOT supported by MSTest v3 (it requires .NET 6+)\n- `net462` — .NET Framework 4.6.2 IS supported by MSTest v3\n- `netcoreapp3.1` — .NET Core 3.1 is NOT supported by MSTest v3\n\n\n- Also, MSTest v3 consolidated its packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages from earlier versions.","outputTokens":518,"requestId":"0BC8:1F2F04:654466B:6E8DCCC:69F01EAF"},"id":"8f857c1d-0267-478f-b6b3-68d1787b25d1","timestamp":"2026-04-28T02:43:06.614Z","parentId":"be5d0e15-1fe1-44e1-a64f-39cebc7a5d90"}
